Mouse Cursor Disappared in Windows
1) Try combination of below keys first
fn+f3 or fn+f9 or fn+f11

2) Update the Mouse driver
	a) Press Win button, type Device Manager. Press Enter on Device Manager
	b) Press Tab and Find "Mice and other pointing devices"
	c) Upon that press, right arrow. You can find Warning Symbol on HID compliant mouse
	d) Press Shift + F10 over that, it will ask update driver, Disable device etc.
	e) Press update driver, once update done your can see the pointer.
